  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I link my valid Aadhaar card to the SBI?",
  "response": "To link your valid Aadhaar card to your State Bank of India (SBI) account, you can follow these steps:\n\n---\n\n### **Online Methods**\n1. **Through SBI Internet Banking:**\n   - Log in to your SBI Internet Banking account.\n   - Navigate to the \"Link your Aadhaar Number\" section under the \"Services\" tab.\n   - Enter your Aadhaar number and validate it using the OTP sent to your registered mobile number.\n   - Once verified, your Aadhaar will be linked to your SBI account.\n\n2. **Through SBI YONO App:**\n   - Open the SBI YONO app and log in.\n   - Go to the \"Services\" section and select \"Aadhaar Linking.\"\n   - Enter your Aadhaar number and verify it using the OTP sent to your registered mobile number.\n   - Your Aadhaar will be linked to your SBI account.\n\n3. **Through SMS:**\n   - Send an SMS in the following format to **567676**:  \n     `UID<space>Aadhaar Number<space>Account Number`  \n     Example: `UID 123456789012 9876543210`\n   - You will receive a confirmation message once the linking is successful.\n\n4. **Through ATM:**\n   - Visit an SBI ATM and swipe your debit card.\n   - Select the \"Aadhaar Seeding\" or \"Aadhaar Linking\" option.\n   - Enter your Aadhaar number and confirm the details.\n   - Your Aadhaar will be linked to your SBI account.\n\n5. **Through SBI Quick (Missed Call Service):**\n   - Give a missed call to **9223766666** from your registered mobile number.\n   - Follow the instructions provided in the SMS you receive to link your Aadhaar.\n\n---\n\n### **Offline Methods**\n1. **Visit an SBI Branch:**\n   - Visit your nearest SBI branch with a copy of your Aadhaar card and your passbook.\n   - Fill out the Aadhaar linking form and submit it to the bank officer.\n   - The bank will process your request and link your Aadhaar to your account.\n\n2. **Through Customer Care:**\n   - Call SBI customer care at **1800 425 3800** or **1800 11 2211**.\n   - Provide your account details and Aadhaar number to link them.\n\n---\n\n### **Documents Required**\n- Aadhaar Card (original and photocopy)\n- SBI Account Passbook or Bank Statement\n- Identity Proof (if required by the bank)\n\n---\n\n### **Important Notes**\n- Ensure that the mobile number registered with your Aadhaar is active to receive the OTP for verification.\n- If your name in Aadhaar and the bank account does not match, you may need to update it at the bank or UIDAI.\n\nOnce the linking is successful, you will receive a confirmation message from SBI.",
